This is a simple program that is used to find the cheapest flights to europe from a given airport code.  It does this by using the kayak.com api to run queries against every aiport code in europe.  

In order to use this, you will need a kayak developer api key which can be obtained very easily here: http://www.kayak.com/labs/api/search/developerkey.html

The usage is as follows:
ruby cheapest_flight_to_europe.rb <DEVELOPER_KEY> AIRPORT_CODE DEPART_DATE RETURN_DATE NUMBER_OF_PASSENGERS

*For example:*
ruby cheapest_flight_to_europe.rb <YOUR_KEY> LAX 12/18/2010 1/1/2011 1


This will return CSV separated list of values of the format:

Price in USD, City, Country, Airport Code, Url To Purchase Tickts

Here are some example results:
